rel_Claim:
10. Method according to claim 1, wherein the coherence enhancing step includes:
- a first substep of computing a coherent data set for each virtual transmit focal zone by applying delays to the raw data for performing a virtual dynamic transmit focusing on said virtual transmit focal zone, assuming that the speed of sound is homogeneous in the region;
- a second substep in which said delays are corrected by an estimation of aberrations in the imaged region based on the coherent data set calculated at the first substep, and the corrected delays are used to compute a new coherent data set by performing a virtual dynamic transmit focusing on said virtual transmit focal zone.

